metadata.name: When we were Kids #5
metadata.description:
When we were kids.

A work that goes back to our childhood.
When I was a kid I loved spending time with my grandmother and parents, we took a lot of walks with them, looked at different houses, spent time in nature, painted and in general were very much involved in the creative component, it was my parents and grandmother who instilled in me a love for creativity.

Probably one of the few things that have survived to these days is my childhood drawings, a little funny, sloppy, but so real and sincere.

In this work I wanted to take me back to those carefree times and remember with what eagerness and zeal I tried every day to learn something new or to go further than before.

None of this would have happened without my family, for which I am truly grateful.

10% of primary sales will be donated to Cure Parkinson's, I hope all children will have a childhood where they can spend time with their loved ones.

Be patient, some variations take a little longer to render.

Press S for Save Canvas as PNG.

By aleks.ustya, @ALEKUSTN. Made with p5js.

metadata.name: Sketches:Pairs of Tails:Majestic Creatures #29
metadata.description:
Addendum to Annuls of WorSAGE (the Worshipful Society of Adventurers and Generative Explorers) XXVII.Vol.2048

There is a significantly common phenomena in which Pairs of "Tails of Majestic Creatures" are found together. Various sketches of these "Pairs" have been collated and are available, free of charge, the collectors of the initial Tails of Majestic Creatures collection based upon a recently taken collection registry snapshot. 

These sketches are available on a one per collector basis and for a limited time only after which they will no longer be accessible.

The sketches come in 2 forms - an ink and color style, and a pencil style - for which different colored paper has been used.

The digitally minded can press s to get a 5000x3000 download of a sketch.

metadata.description:
I wanted to continue the "Flore" series, taking inspiration from my artwork "Florescentia." This second "Flores" was conceived with elements from the first, but with added chaos and uncertainty.

Press "s" to save a png

metadata.name: hippieCircles #1
metadata.description:
Hippie Circles is a trip back in time to a genre of imagery I recall from my coming of age in the 1960's; psychedelic art. Bright colors and images that would blow your mind. Especially if influenced by a few tokes.

This image consists of several tessellated layers a concentric circle tile. The palette is limited to a few bright colors. I find the image remarkably simple yet visually complex at the same time. Every iteration is a new trip. Far out!

I hope you enjoy my flashback.

Please visit www.drbillkolomyjec.com

metadata.description:

"Chasing the Sunset" explores the timeless pursuit of capturing the sun's fleeting beauty as it rises and sets, reminding us of the constant ebb and flow of time and light

metadata.name: Framed Flowers #42
metadata.description:
A geometrical flower displayed in a colorfull frame. Or the opposite.

Variations include :
- 10 different color palettes
- Light or dark background
- Rare « negative » mode
- Aerial, Diamond, Round, Squared frames in various combinations
- 8 types of flower shapes, with various modifiers, some duality
- And much more !

metadata.name: 70s Tapestry #2
metadata.description:
70s Tapestry is a tribute to the fine art work of embroiderers, and the 70s design.

- 3 types of embroidery tile type distribution
- and some special rare traits

metadata.name: Julia's Magical Bulbs - 3rd 4th 5th Powers #13
metadata.description:
Julia's Magical Bulbs are 3D dimensional fractals, based on the Julia Sets of the Mandelbulb fractal.  In this edition we explore the 3rd, 4th and 5th powers.

The token is interactive, use your mouse-wheel to zoom-in and see all the little details. You will find a menu in the lower-right corner which allows you to play with the iterations and camera position. You can also render high-resolution images here.

A little bit of magic happens when you select low iteration values, perhaps your token will even default to this.

Technical:

Not all browsers support multi-threaded modules, the fallback mode is quite slow. Try Chrome if your browser is not supported.

Calculated in full 64-bit on the CPU (not the GPU) for more accurate and detailed images.
